. Locking a ``hot Jupiter'' in an isolated spin-orbit resonance is\nunlikely at 0.05 AU but could be possible at larger distances. Another\nmechanism is then required to maintain a large obliquity and create internal\nheating through obliquity tides\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Dec 2006 21:58:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
